MACINTOSH SE

•	What year was it made? 
1987
•	What operating system does it run? 
3.3-3.4, 4.0–6.0.2, 6.0.3–6.0.8, 7.0-7.5.5
•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List). 
Then, it cost US$2900 (dual floppy) and US$3900 (with 20 MB hard drive), which today would be USD $6074.30 and $8168.89, repectively. The first computer I saw on eBay was selling for USD $ 1,300! There were none for sale in the DC area on craigslist. 
•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for?
It seems that this computer is best known for being to accomodate 2 (and 3 in the case of SE) floppy disks. Some of its upgrades are an "internal drive bay," a keyboard and mouse, faster processing, more relable and long lasting and a cooling fan for temperature regulation. Compared to the Classic that would replace it, the SE was slow and expensive. 
Turn it on (you must figure out how). Read some of Deena Larsen’s Marble Springs. Quit Marble Springs. What else is on this Mac?

I read some of Marble Springs and explored Story Space (moon to Deena), We Descend and some of the standard apps (calculator and alarm clock were the only ones that opened, and the rest took up too much memory, lol). I tried to use some of the applications like "Graph Maker," but it appears the computer doesn't have the necessary cards for such applications. 
