AMIGA

•	What year was it made? 
Made in 1985 but not released oficially until 1986. 
•	What operating system does it run? 
AmigaOS
•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List). 
US$1295 + US$300 (Monitor), which would be USD $2863.74 and USD $663.42. Their price on ebay ranged from USD $300.00 - $6,000.00
•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for?
According to wikipedia the Amiga was a great bargin-- it was affordable given the extensive operations it was capable of. It was well known for video editing software and for home computers (games). It seems that the company's innvoative edge sputtered out. They went bankrupt on a model that failed. 
Turn it on (you must figure out how). Try the demos. What else can it do? (Hint: try the “Amiga Appetizer” disk). Have a look at the Amiga magazines and the book, The Future Was Here.

I foundt his a little harder to get up and runnning...

